Use the standard library
This is how to factorize of n:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that d is 2
   Remember that x is n
   Do this n times:
      When product of d and d is more than x, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
      Do this n times:
         Remember that r is remainder of x and d
         When r is 0, then:
            Add result to d
            Remember that x is quotient of x and d
         But, if not:
            Leave the loop
         End when
      End do
      Increase d
   End do
   When x is more than 1, then:
      Add result to x
   End when
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> factorize of 8
[2, 2, 2]
>>> factorize of 25
[5, 5]
>>> factorize of 70
[2, 5, 7]